---
import InstructionNote from '../InstructionNote.astro';
---
<section id="voice">
    <h2>Voice & Language</h2>
    
    <InstructionNote>
        Define the reading level and communication style of your brand. Create a "Do / Don't" list for plain language, and set structural rules for formatting social media.
    </InstructionNote>

    <h3>Plain Language Guidelines</h3>
    <p>[Describe the target reading level and general tone of the brand. Provide guidelines on jargon, complex sentence structures, etc.]</p>

    <div class="table-responsive">
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th scope="col">Do Say (Inclusive/Plain)</th>
                <th scope="col">Don't Say (Exclusionary/Idiom)</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Clothing swaps are a great way to refresh your wardrobe without 
                spending money. When you swap instead of shop new, you keep clothes 
                out of the trash and reduce waste.</td>
                <td>Clothing swaps are a cornerstone of a circular fashion 
                ecosystem that diverts textiles from the waste stream.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Repairing a piece of clothing gives it a longer life so it stays out of the landfill. 
                A simple fix means you get more use out of something you already own.</td>
                <td>Mending garments extends their lifecycle and mitigates the environmental 
                impact of fast fashion's throwaway culture.</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    </div>
</section>